<chapter condition="TITLE=Services: Facility Maintenance;PERM=sy_bank_facility_access"
           id="FAM" role="TOPIC">
  <title>Facility Maintenance</title>

  <section role="ITEM">
    <title>Overview</title>

    <para role="TEXT">As an administrator at a bank, you can add a credit
    facility that banks give their customers and allocate limits across the
    customer's various branches. At this moment, this feature is applicable
    only for Banker Guarantee.</para>
 </section>
    <section role="ITEM">
      <title>Facility Maintenance - Navigation</title>

      <para role="TEXT">To navigate to the <emphasis role="bold">Facility
      Maintenance</emphasis> function, from the toolbar, select
      <emphasis>System Features</emphasis> from the home page, then select
      <emphasis>Facility Maintenance</emphasis> from the left navigation
      menu.</para>
    </section>

    <section role="ITEM">
      <title>Facility Maintenance - Customer Facility List</title>

      <para role="TEXT">This option is used by the Bank Administrator and the
      Bank Group Administrator to Maintain Facility details for customers.
      When you select this option, you are presented with a list of all the
      existing customers at your bank or bank group. You can search the list
      by entering search criteria in the <guilabel moreinfo="none">Abbreviated
      Name</guilabel>, <guilabel>Bank</guilabel>, <guilabel>Facility
      Reference</guilabel>, <guilabel>Ccy</guilabel>.,
      <guilabel>Facility</guilabel> and <guilabel>Review Date</guilabel>
      fields at the top of the page. Click the <guilabel>Download
      File</guilabel> button to download the list in CSV and Spreadsheet (MS
      Excel) format.</para>

      <para role="TEXT">The list of existing customers has the following
      columns:</para>

      <informaltable role="TEXT">
        <tgroup cols="2">
          <colspec colname="c1" colwidth="2.0*" />

          <colspec colname="c2" colwidth="8.0*" />

          <thead>
            <row>
              <entry valign="top"><para>Field</para></entry>

              <entry valign="top"><para>Description</para></entry>
            </row>
          </thead>

          <tbody>
            <row>
              <entry valign="top"><para> <guilabel moreinfo="none">Abbreviated
              Name</guilabel> </para></entry>

              <entry valign="top"><para>Abbreviated name that uniquely
              identifies the customer. This is part of the login data that a
              customer user must give to log into <xi:include
              href="../entities_en.xml" xpointer="ent_appli"
              xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude" />.</para></entry>
            </row>

            <row>
              <entry valign="top"><para> <guilabel
              moreinfo="none">Name</guilabel> </para></entry>

              <entry valign="top"><para>Name of the customer.</para></entry>
            </row>
          </tbody>
        </tgroup>
      </informaltable>

      <para role="TEXT">You can access further details for a customer by
      clicking on the required row. You are displayed the <guilabel>Customer
      Facility List</guilabel> with the details shown in the table
      below.</para>

      <informaltable role="TEXT">
        <tgroup cols="2">
          <colspec colname="c1" colwidth="2.0*" />

          <colspec colname="c2" colwidth="8.0*" />

          <thead>
            <row>
              <entry valign="top"><para>Field</para></entry>

              <entry valign="top"><para>Description</para></entry>
            </row>
          </thead>

          <tbody>
            <row>
              <entry valign="top"><para> <guilabel moreinfo="none">Facility
              Reference</guilabel> </para></entry>

              <entry valign="top"><para>The reference details for the
              facility. </para></entry>
            </row>

            <row>
              <entry valign="top"><para> <guilabel moreinfo="none">Facility
              Description</guilabel> </para></entry>

              <entry valign="top"><para>The description for the
              facility.</para></entry>
            </row>

            <row>
              <entry valign="top"><para> <guilabel
              moreinfo="none">Bank</guilabel> </para></entry>

              <entry valign="top">The Group Bank or Bank selected to maintain
              this facility.</entry>
            </row>

            <row>
              <entry valign="top"><para> <guilabel moreinfo="none">Facility
              Review Date</guilabel> </para></entry>

              <entry valign="top">The future date to review the extension of
              the facility to the customer. If not extended by this date, the
              facility is withdrawn automatically.</entry>
            </row>

            <row>
              <entry valign="top"><para> <guilabel
              moreinfo="none">Ccy</guilabel> </para></entry>

              <entry valign="top">The base currency for the facility.</entry>
            </row>

            <row>
              <entry valign="top"><para> <guilabel moreinfo="none">Facility
              Amount</guilabel> </para></entry>

              <entry valign="top">The amount allocated to the
              facility.</entry>
            </row>

            <row>
              <entry valign="top"><para> <guilabel moreinfo="none">Available
              Amount</guilabel> </para></entry>

              <entry valign="top">The balance amount available after
              utilisation by the customer.</entry>
            </row>

            <row>
              <entry valign="top"><para> <guilabel moreinfo="none">Utilized
              Amount</guilabel> </para></entry>

              <entry valign="top">The amount utilised out of the total
              allocated by the bank to the facility.</entry>
            </row>

            <row>
              <entry valign="top"><para> <guilabel moreinfo="none">Pending
              Bank Amount</guilabel> </para></entry>

              <entry valign="top">The amount that is awaiting approval by the
              bank. <note>
                  <para>This information is available if the configuration has
                  been set by the application administrator to wait for
                  approval by the bank. However, if the administrator has set
                  it for direct submission by the customer, this field is not
                  applicable.</para>
                </note></entry>
            </row>

            <row>
              <entry valign="top"><para> <guilabel
              moreinfo="none">Utilization(Pct)</guilabel> </para></entry>

              <entry valign="top">The percentage utilised out of the total
              amount allocated.</entry>
            </row>

            <row>
              <entry valign="top"><para> <guilabel moreinfo="none">Linked
              Entities</guilabel> </para></entry>

              <entry valign="top">Entities linked to the facility.</entry>
            </row>

            <row>
              <entry
              valign="top"><para><guilabel>Status</guilabel></para></entry>

              <entry valign="top"><para>This indicates the status of the
              facility, whether, it is active or inactive. </para></entry>
            </row>

            <row>
              <entry valign="top"><para><guilabel>Maker User
              </guilabel></para></entry>

              <entry valign="top"><para>Displays the user ID of the maker of
              the transaction.</para><note>
                  <para>This column is only available if maker-checker
                  functionality is enabled.</para>
                </note></entry>
            </row>
          </tbody>
        </tgroup>
      </informaltable>

      <para role="TEXT">You can modify a facility by clicking the <guiicon
      moreinfo="none">Edit</guiicon> <inlinemediaobject>
          <imageobject>
            <imagedata fileref="../images/icon_edit.gif" role="ICON_EDIT"
                       width="4mm" />
          </imageobject>
        </inlinemediaobject> icon in the right-hand column, view it in
      non-editable mode by clicking the <guibutton>View</guibutton>
      <inlinemediaobject>
          <imageobject>
            <imagedata fileref="../images/icon_popup.gif" role="ICON_POPUP"
                       width="4.5mm" />
          </imageobject>
        </inlinemediaobject> icon, or delete it by clicking the <guibutton
      moreinfo="none">Delete</guibutton> <inlinemediaobject>
          <imageobject>
            <imagedata fileref="../images/icon_trash.gif" role="ICON_TRASH"
                       width="4mm" />
          </imageobject>
        </inlinemediaobject> icon. Click the <guibutton moreinfo="none">Add a
      new Facility</guibutton> button at the bottom of the list to add a
      facility. <guiicon moreinfo="none">Edit</guiicon> and <guibutton
      moreinfo="none">Add a new Facility </guibutton>display the same form,
      but in the case of <guibutton moreinfo="none">Edit</guibutton>, the
      <guilabel>Bank Name</guilabel> and <guilabel>Customer
      Reference</guilabel> fields are not editable.</para>

      <para role="TEXT">Cancel a transaction by clicking on the
      <guibutton>Cancel</guibutton> <inlinemediaobject>
          <imageobject>
            <imagedata fileref="../images/icon_makerchecker_cancel.gif" />
          </imageobject>
        </inlinemediaobject> icon or approve by clicking the
      <guibutton>Action</guibutton> <inlinemediaobject>
          <imageobject>
            <imagedata fileref="../images/icon_makerchecker_action.gif" />
          </imageobject>
        </inlinemediaobject> icon. These icons are available if maker-checker
      is enabled for your profile.</para>

